			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> paper:</span><br><i>Specializing Scope Graph Resolution Queries</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/AronZwaan.html">Aron Zwaan</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3567523">10.1145/3567512.3567523</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagM">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It improves name-resolution/type-checking (static semantics) via specialized scope-graph queries.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5f.html"><span class="tagL">T5F: Performance</span></a><ul><li> The specialization targets faster, more scalable resolution/query execution.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagL">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> Scope graphs act as a metalanguage/formalism for describing name binding and resolution.
</li></ul></li></ul>
